  "text": "Only those polymorphic protein changes that are neutral to cell fitness, or became neutral because of the buffering effect of chaperones [CITATION_1] , will persist in a growing liquid culture. Indeed, the excess PC (over the wild type level) in the mutH mutator strain is subject to larger effects of chaperone deletions and over-expressions than in the wild type strain ( Figure 1A) . Hence, by measuring PC, we can detect the consequences of random protein imperfections occurring during their biosynthesis and folding, as well as of recurrent specific protein imperfections encoded by mutant genes.",
